Subject: The Future of Bionics
Description: In the beginning, bionics were expensive things sold by large companies. Now, we're 3D printing them for less than a fancy dinner, and soon, we're going to be controlling them with our minds! What will the future hold for people who use these devices to make their lives richer? Will we be bionic people? Will we be better...stronger...faster?  Speakers include:Cynthia Chestek, Albert Manero, Jen Owen, Ivan Owen - Track: Science  - Duration: 50 minutes - Audio/video needs: none

Subject: Building Hands for Our Charity
Description: Come help our charity assemble hands, fresh off the 3D printers, which we will teach you to assemble! Join Jen, Ivan, Albert, our local e-Nable volunteer Aaron, and some of the Penguicon Con Committee as we thread cables and melt plastic. Also learn how you can print and assemble hands, at home, for those helped by Enabling the Future!  Speakers include:Jen Owen, Ivan Owen, Albert Manero, Aaron Brown - Track: Tech  - Duration: 1 hour and 50 minutes - Audio/video needs: none

Subject: Using Your Geek for Good Instead of Evil
Description: You're the leetest of leet. You dream in code. Instead of helping prolong the problems of corporations for fun and money or creating state sponsored malware, what kind of good can you do with your skills? Why bother? Come listen to some people who are changing the world by sharing their technical abilities with others.   Speakers include:Nancy Bright, Erika Carlson, Emily Gonyer, Ken Grundberg, Albert Manero, Jen Owen, Ivan Owen - Track: Life  - Duration: 50 minutes - Audio/video needs: none
